<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Liverpool’s Premier League clash with Arsenal on Monday night is being moved from an 8.15pm kick off to 8pm due to the Government’s lockdown measures on pubs.</p>

<p>The closure of bars at 10pm meant supporters would have potentially missed the final minutes of the match.</p>

<p>But the Premier League are expected to announce that the tie, which will be shown live on Sky Sports, will kick off earlier to avoid this situation. </p>

<p>More to follow. </p>

